Entry and borders
See Entry requirements to find out what you will need to do when you arrive in Grenada.
Travel in Grenada
Government announced a limited State of Emergency from 25 March. There have been recent measures announced to relax the restrictions. This includes business days being extended to every day, reduction of curfew from 24 hrs to 9pm to 5am daily, and a limited ferry service to Carriacou and Petit Martinique. Everyone must observe social distancing and wear a face mask when out in public. You should keep up to date with changes to the Emergency Powers Regulations on the Government Information Service Facebook page.
Healthcare in Grenada
The Ministry of Health Grenada is asking the public to call the COVID-19 enquiries information line on 538 4787 or 458 4787 or the police on 440 3999 if they have any symptoms such as cough fever or difficulty breathing.
For contact details for English speaking doctors visit our list of healthcare providers.
Your emotional and mental wellbeing is important. Read guidance on how to look after your mental wellbeing and mental health.
